node.text: Having missed the first train by mere minutes, I spent the next three hours waiting for the next to pass. Thankfully, it was worth it. Shot with the #Mavic2Zoom 🚈🌴 @djiglobal #SeeTheBiggerPicture

There’s something about China that keeps drawing me back... so much so that we are returning to Beijing this week to celebrate Chinese New Year! If you had to spend the rest of your life in one country, which would it be and why? 📚

Our first few days in Sri Lanka with @skyhour have been hectic- so much so that I’m nearly falling asleep whilst writing this caption, but what a journey it’s been so far! We’ve got some really exciting new projects coming up over the next few weeks, including some frequently requested tutorials. I can’t wait to share our upcoming plans, and a huge thank you to everyone for supporting us along the way ❤️

These sandstone towers in Saudi Arabia absolutely blew me away. Found within the largest continuous sand desert in the world, I can only imagine what else is out there. Have you ever been to the desert? 🐪 @winterattantora #winterattantora

The shores of Flores are home to a handful of the world’s few pink beaches, which have some of the clearest waters I’ve seen. It’s great to finally be back on the road again and I can’t wait to explore more of Indonesia this year 🐟

node.text: For around 2,000 years this tomb has stood alone in the Saudi desert. As I sat there, I couldn’t help but wonder how on Earth it would have been built all that time ago... 🏚🐪 @winterattantora #winterattantora

Wandering through Tokyo’s very own lantern forest was one of the most unique experiences I’ve had to date. Tomorrow we are back on the road for the foreseeable future, starting our journey in Sri Lanka - I cant wait to get started! 💡💎 #whpwanderlust

The last few days out here in Saudi Arabia have been an absolute whirlwind. From flying high above the space-like landscapes in a helicopter, to sipping tea with the Bedouins, this place has surpassed all expectations ✨ @winterattantora #winterattantora
🎉 Thank you for everyone who entered the giveaway! Congratulations to the winner @pradhannishal 🎉

node.text: Our trip to South Dakota over the weekend with @visittheusa surpassed all expectations, particularly the landscape at Badlands National Park which blew us away. I can’t wait to head back to the States for a road trip later in the year. Which state would you recommend we visit next and why?! 🇺🇸 #UnitedStories

After a crazy few days out in South Dakota, I’m now back in England for the next 24 hours before heading out to Saudi Arabia. You’ll be pleased to know I will finally be sharing some new photos starting this week! Cheers to the start of another jam-packed year 🙌🏻
I remember walking along this beach in Nusa Penida without another person in sight, and it reminded me just how lucky we are to call this earth home. Which is your favourite beach? 🌊
As the day drew to a close the crowds slowly drifted away, leaving this one guy with the place all to himself. I can’t wait to head back to the Middle East one day soon - any suggestions guys? 🐪

This is the kind of place I’d like to spend these long winter days... how about you? On a side note, after months of hibernation, we are finally back on the road tomorrow! Over the next few weeks we’ll be hitting up South Dakota, Saudi Arabia and Sri Lanka, so let me know if you’re going to be around! 🍃🏚

We’ve been back in Europe for two weeks now, and are really missing Indonesia and our cats. This was taken in Java, an island I’m incredibly excited to explore more next month. Anyone want to join? 🌝 #whpunexpected

Taking it back to a very cold morning in Zhangjiajie, China. We have just arrived in Budapest ready for a weekend of thermal baths and ruin bars, and have ticked another European country off the list. What are you guys up to this weekend? 🎉

Thinking back to those crisp Bavarian mornings spent shooting from sunrise to sunset with a good bunch of friends... nothing beats it. I can’t wait to head back to Germany for some snow this month! 🌲🍁
Hello 2019! After last night’s festivities, I’m so so excited for a new year full of fresh opportunities. How did you guys celebrate the coming of the New Year? 👩🏻‍🌾🐃

With 2018 soon coming to an end, it’s crazy to look back on all of the challenges and triumphs the past year has brought my way; none of which I would change for the world. It’s been crammed with opportunities to work some dream jobs, meet and befriend incredible people, learn a whole load about myself and truly focus on where I want to go in life. I’m also eternally grateful for the undying support I’ve had this year from those close to me, and from those I am yet to meet, including all of you guys; either way, you know who you are. Looking forward to seeing you guys on the other side - let’s make 2019 the best year yet! 🥂🎆

What a year 2018 has been. I think my biggest achievement has been being able to cross off so many new places in China, with one of my goals for next year being to visit the remaining provinces and put together a China photo book! What are your goals for 2019? 🎇
One of my favourite trips this year was to Jordan; a place I have wanted to visit since I found out there was a country with the same name as me. What’s top of your bucket list for 2019? 🌎

I can only imagine what spending Christmas morning here would feel like... On another note, happy holidays to all of you! I hope you’re having an incredibly festive time surrounded by family and friends, wherever you are. Excuse me while I get back to the most important task of the day, stuffing my face 🏡🍂
Why did the camel cross the road? Oh, and Happy Christmas Eve, everyone. How are you preparing for the big day tomorrow? 🐪

I hope everyone is having a great weekend wherever in the world you may be, and that your festivities are in full swing! I’m currently stuffing myself with delicious food with my family and looking back at some of my favourite moments this year...🐟🐠 #WHPmagical

node.text: One of my main goals for 2019 is to finally visit every province in China! This was from a morning spent far out in West Sichuan, on a hill above the largest gathering of monks and nuns in the world. How about you? 🏚👲🏽

From a still evening on the shores of the Li River. On another note, it’s great to finally be back home! I’m pretty excited to spend the next two weeks in hibernation, editing the thousands of photos left over from the last few months! 🎄

After a few fun-filled days of adventuring in Kuala Lumpur, it’s finally time to head home for Christmas! I can’t wait to spend some time with the family and eat my own body weight in food. What are your plans for the festive season? 🌈🎄

Foggy autumnal mornings in the Chinese countryside. For all of you photographers and other creators out there, please check my stories for a scam I was recently fooled by. It may one day save you from learning a very expensive lesson! Have a great week, my friends! 🏡🍂

It’s strange to think that today was our last day in Bali this year. While I always seem to have an urge to travel elsewhere, I’m kind of sad to be leaving the great friends we’ve made and of course, the cats. After so many years on the road it’s great to finally be able to call a place home. Next stop, Malaysia! 🌴
While I’d like to think I’ve already seen a fair portion of China, I’d be wrong... can’t wait to get back in 2019, as I have so much more to show you all! Who’s ready for the new year? 👩🏻‍🌾🐕

Afternoon light shining bright on one of my favourite roads. Speaking of which, I’m currently planning a road trip through Germany for January - seriously hoping for some snow! Any places we should definitely check out? 🐉

We spent a total of 12 hours roaming around the ancient ruins of Petra, exploring all we possibly could. On our way out, I couldn’t help but notice this lady observing the beauty of Petra’s monastery, and while she’ll see it seven days a week, I can’t blame her for taking another look 🧕🏽🐪
As the sun broke over the Indian Ocean, this entire scene lit up before my tired eyes. Note the fisherman’s boat heading out for a day’s work - that’s one hell of a commute 🚣🏼‍♂️ #whpnaturallight

Endless sweeping dunes and towering sandstone mountains make the Wadi Rum one of the most beautiful places one earth. On another note, big up @sophiapope for putting up with me for the past 4 years - no idea how she’s managed it! 🧡
This may well be the ultimate Hot Wheels track. What’s the coolest road you’ve ever driven on? 🚙
If you had to spend a week in the desert alone, which three things would you take and why? For me, it would have to be pancakes, tea, and more pancakes! 🥞☕️

Having driven across this intersection on multiple occasions during my stay in Chengdu, it was only on my last day that I decided to launch the drone - and it sure blew me away! Anyone out there brave enough to tackle this road?! 🚖🚘 #chengdu

I just got back to Bali this morning after the busiest month - can’t wait for some down time this month and to begin planning for 2019. We have some big things on the horizon that I can’t wait to share with you. What do you want to see from us next year? 🤟🏼

It was great to spend the last two days back in @chengdu_china . With it being one of my favourite Chinese cities, it’s amazing to see that they’re now introducing the 144 hour transit visa - such a game changer for exploring Western China! Also, who’s down for a game up there? 🇨🇳⚽️

Southern China has some of the most jaw-dropping karst landscapes on the planet. I’m thinking about running a China photography workshop next year and would love to know who would be interested in attending? 🇨🇳

As a sandstorm emerged in the distance, we found this century-old train making it’s way through the soft dunes of the Wadi Rum desert in Jordan. If you’ve ever considered taking a train through heaven on Earth, here’s your place! 🚂

Reflection perfection in the Chinese countryside. I found out this evening that I’ll be flying back to China tomorrow - nothing like a bit of spontaneity. Do you prefer to plan your trips to a T or just go with the flow? 🌲🍂
Having spent the last week in the Middle East, I know for sure I’ll be back in 2019 for a load more adventures. Which countries should we visit next?🧕🏽🐪
We found a real book, can you believe it?! Huge thanks to @sophiapope for always unwillingly modelling in my photos. What should I get her for Christmas? 🎄

It was great to finally tick something off the bucket list yesterday as we explored the Ancient City of Petra, and it was truly more magical than I could have ever imagined. What’s at the top of your bucket list? 🇯🇴
Just another mystical afternoon in China. How are you guys starting off your week? ✨
Sometimes, all you need is a little bit of luck. The midmorning sunlight trickled through these ancient banyan trees for a matter of 10 seconds, lighting up the scene perfectly before us! 🐃
Sometimes I struggle to comprehend how incredible Mother Nature is. In the past year, which one place has amazed you the most? 🌳
While our time in Japan was brief, we were lucky to find the valleys of Nagano in full bloom. This has to be one of the most idyllic train journeys in the world, right? 🚂
After all of these chilly mornings the last few months, I’m looking forward to warmer days like this. Who’s with me? 🏝 #WHPSeasonal

node.text: This morning was a special one. As we walked the perimeter of the lake, we couldn’t help but notice the burning shades of red orange foliage come in to full bloom. Already planning my return for the cherry blossoms, who’s with me? 🍁🗻 #WHPSeasonal
Tokyo is quickly becoming my favourite city in the world. This is my fourth trip to Japan in two years, and I still can’t get enough! Which is your favourite city in the world and why? 🌏🚕

After 3 weeks of travelling through Eastern China, we have now made it to Japan thanks to @skyhour! We will be shooting the autumn colours in and around Tokyo for the next week, and can’t wait to bring you all along for the ride. Any recommendations for Tokyo?!👇🏻🇯🇵

Crisp mornings at the Temple of Heaven. If you hadn’t heard, @josiahwg and I will be hosting a photography workshop in Costa Rica from January 16th-23rd. There we shall teach you all we know in one of the most bio diverse places on the planet! Link in my bio for more info 🀄️
Made in China. After being able to wander around the magnificent Binhai Library all alone, I’d say the early wake up was totally worth it! 📚 #whpscale

The Great Wall is one of those places that amazes you every time you visit, and we were lucky enough to get this section to ourselves as the sun began to set. Which of the Seven Wonders is highest on your list? 🇨🇳 #whpscale

Golden hour lighting up the stand alone pines of Huangshan. As our time in China comes to an end, it’s been crazy to reflect on everything we’ve seen the past few weeks. It’s fair to say we are well and truly exhausted! ⛰

Fall in China is upon us! We spent the past few days hiking around Huangshan, China’s most revered mountain range. It was only on the way back that we spotted this road from the cable car, and made sure our driver took a slight detour home. Oh, and happy birthday Mum! You’re the best 🍃🍁
I’ve been wanting to take a photo like this since I first came to China three years ago - what a wild ride it’s been since then. What’s your dream photograph?! 🐃🐕
Can’t wait to see this place in the snow next year! I had approximately 6 seconds to get this shot, which was taken from a very shaky cable car in the depths of China. How did I do? 🚠
Without another foreign tourist in sight, we’ve spent the last few days exploring the colourful fishing villages of China’s east coast. Here’s to more mornings like this! 🚣🏻‍♂️
The Chinese countryside is full of surprises... These traditional Tulous can hold up to 100 families. Who’s down to house share? 💃
Flying high above the hashtags of Hong Kong. If you could see one destination from the sky, where would it be and why? 🚁

This wasn’t my typical sunrise mission. It actually involved my Dad and I waking up at 3am to ride a bicycle 30km through complete darkness - great memories that will last a life time. Anyone down to join for a sunrise paddle? 🗻🚣🏻‍♂️
Just a few hours from the North Korean border lies the largest wetland in the world. The autumn colours aren’t so bad either! 🌳🍁

node.text: The last six months have been pretty full on and packed with work. While I’ll always appreciate being able to do what I love for a living, it’s also so refreshing to break away from the deadlines and to focus on personal trips. With the next few weeks full of new adventures, I am way too excited to share it all with you! 🙋🏻‍♂️

One of my favourite afternoons from the past year was spent wandering the Halls of the Sheik Zayed Mosque, accompanied by the beautiful Call to Prayer. With only a few months left in 2018, what plans do you have for the rest of the year? 🕌

node.text: Finally headed back to this incredible country. Can’t wait to show you guys China’s autumn colours! 🍃🍁
Our last morning down on the Gold Coast was one to remember. We watched the locals head out for their early morning surf before work - not a bad life... 🏄🏻‍♂️ @destinationgoldcoast @statravel
This whale mother and her calf were just a few hundred meters from the coastline... 🐳 @destinationgoldcoast @statravel
While it’s been great to relax at home, I’m so keen for the next adventure. Where are you guys planning on spending the autumn? I’m headed to China and Japan! 🍃

The sand really is this pink. We took a group of friends over to Flores last month for a boat trip and got to spend the afternoon on one of the most pristine beaches in Indonesia. Where’s your favourite beach and why? 💕

node.text: Today we applied for Chinese visas - hoping so badly we can fly back next week for a month of adventures! Whose ready for some autumn colours in China? 🍂
Shadow play over beaches as far the eye can see. If I had to choose a superpower, it would definitely be to fly! How about you?🏙🌊 @destinationgoldcoast @statravel
Sailing around these islands with good friends is a recipe for good times. From pink sand beaches to Komodo dragons, Flores has to be one of the world’s greatest natural treasures @floresiatrip 🐉

The perfect morning commute. I remember this morning so clearly. Having planned visiting this location for months, we set out in complete darkness only to get lost along the way. For three hours we pushed onwards while stopping to ask multiple strangers if they knew the way. Sometimes all you need is the smallest bit of luck for everything to come together 🐃

I guess it’s one of the New 7 Wonders of the World for a reason. I’ve been listening to @lewishowes podcasts a lot recently, and a summarised quote from his most recent upload got me thinking - “don’t worry about the numbers, just add value to the followers that you already have”. So guys, what do you want to see from me next? I’d love to hear!✌🏼

node.text: In the name of International Peace Day, here’s a throwback to this colourful character. Monks are my favourite subject to shoot! What’s yours? 🏛✌🏼
There’s nothing like an early morning on the Australian coast. Who would love to spend their summer here? 🏚🏖

Just two days until we head back to Flores, the land of Komodo dragons and the most pristine water I’ve ever seen. It’s one of those places that has to be seen to be believed, and I can’t wait to share more! 🐉
Flying high above the Black Spur Drive certainly shows the enormity of the place. It’s been the most incredible 10 days out here in Australia; time to head back to Bali! 🌲🍃
Tropical sunsets in Southern Thailand earlier this year. Where’s your favourite place for a beach holiday? 🌴
Singapore’s architecture never fails to amaze me - thanks so much for having us, @jwmarriottsg! Which city has your favourite architecture? 🏙🌿

This was the perfect ending to a day spent driving along the Great Ocean Road, one of the world’s most scenic coastal drives. Also, I’ll be taking over the @moodygrams account tomorrow, so be sure to come say hey! 🐨🌊

node.text: It’s times like this that remind me why waking up for sunrise isn’t such a bad idea. Spent the last few days bombing around Australia - can’t wait to share the photos with you all soon! 🍃
Local life is by far my favourite thing to photograph. Also, we are finally headed to a new country tomorrow! Any guesses where? 🎣

Shadow play in southern China. This was taken the morning after I replaced my runaway drone. When I got back to the hotel, I realised I’d shot it all in JPEG, then my memory card crashed. What’s the worst luck you’ve had on the road? 🍃
Undoubtedly the most exhausting hike of my life led to the most beautiful evening. Check out my stories for the long-awaited Peru series 🇵🇪 #WHPcolorpalette
Having spent the majority of the last two years in Bali, it’s been great to finally show my Dad around the island! Experiencing a small creative block right now, any tips to overcome this? 🌋

Friends, my new website is now live! Head over to the link in my bio for my all-new Lightroom Mobile and Desktop Presets, and remember to use the code ‘JORD30’ for 30% off (48hours only). For now, it’s time for a beer, or five! 🏖🍻

After a long wait and many, many hours of hard work, my new website will be launching tomorrow at 1300GMT! There you’ll be able to download my new mobile and desktop preset packs, order prints and read my photo itineraries to everywhere I’ve travelled over the last year. There will also be a big discount for the first 48 hours, so stay tuned! 🚣🏻‍♂️⛰
Welcome to South America’s only desert oasis. If you were stranded here for the rest of your life and could only take three things with you, what would they be and why? 🌵🐪
Misty mornings over the crater lake of Mount Ijen. Soph and I had to sprint up the volcano to catch the sunrise- I think it was worth it! 🌋

node.text: There’s something about these colourful cityscapes that I find so aesthetically pleasing. Also, I’m having a hard time deciding between Canon and Sony right now... any advice? 📸
If you had to spend the rest of your life in one country, which would it be and why? 🌿
The incredible rainbow village of Jodipan. Which house would you live in? 🏚🌈 @traveloka

First light amongst the terraces. While it’s amazing to call this island home, my feet are becoming super itchy with the need for a new adventure. What have you guys got planned for the rest of 2018? 🌾
Nature’s framing. The cherry blossoms in Japan absolutely blew me away. It’s one thing seeing it in photographs, but another to experience it. Who wants to visit Japan? 🌸
I feel so lucky to have watched this sunrise with my Dad last summer, such a great memory. Looking forward to getting him out to Bali next week - any suggestions for our trip together? 🌿🌊

Early morning strolls amongst the vast dunes of The Empty Quarter. Just to remind you guys, registration for my Jordan workshop this November closes soon! From the ancient city of Petra, to the stillness of the Dead Sea, it’s going to be such an adventure. Check the link in my bio for more information! 🐪
East Java reminds me of a scene from ‘The Land Before Time’. Who was your favourite character? For me, it’s Petrie 🦕

As I’m sure you have all heard, there has recently been a series of devastating earthquakes over in neighbouring Lombok. The residents are in serious need of help, so please do consider sparing any change you have! Follow the link in my bio and stories to donate ❤️
I’m seriously debating going back to this place in the next few months. The question is, autumn leaves or fresh snow? 🍁❄️
Guys! My next photography workshop is fast approaching and this time it’s in Jordan, from November 18th-25th. Head on over to the link in my bio to sign up! 🌵
Magical mornings on Mount Bromo. As the sun came up, a puff of smoke from a distant volcano was illuminated. East Java is truly phenomenal 🌋💨 @traveloka
The otherworldly landscapes of Guangxi seem almost as though they’re a painting. In other news, we’ve spent the day planning our trip to Africa later this year! Any suggestions? 👨🏻‍🌾🐃
Congratulations to the winner, @ray.roper! Big thanks again to all of you who took part. Stay tuned for the next giveaway! 🙌🏼 @passporterapp

The rainbow village of Jodipan. Just last year this place was on the verge of eviction. Fortunately for the residents, a group of local students partnered up with a paint company and came to the rescue. Pretty cool, huh? 🌈 @traveloka

One of China’s greatest design concepts, otherwise known as The Stairway to Heaven. Who thinks this would make a good wallpaper?! I’ve partnered with @huaweimobileservicesglobal to celebrate the #Honor10 Global Theme Design Contest. Head over to my stories and vote for which theme is your favourite. Visit www.hihonor.com/global/theme for more inspiration. #ExploreMore #HUAWEI #Honor
My first time shooting a lunar event was certainly one for the books. Who else witnessed this absolute magic? 🌓 #WHPLight
Just imagine rediscovering this place back in 1911... I’m certain my brain would have melted. Big thanks to @solylunahotel for having me! ⛰

node.text: I can’t quite believe that there are 300,000 of you following my journey. I hope to have brought you many laughs along the way, and cannot thank you enough for all the support. Air hugs and kisses to you all. It’s now time for a beer (or two!) 🍻

node.text: The palm-lined backwaters of Southern India - there’s no wonder it’s known as ‘God’s own country’. Can’t wait to go back to this incredible place one day! 🌴🚣🏻‍♂️
The first light of day was such a welcome sight after hiking through the darkness to see this place at sunrise. How many colours can you count? ⛰🎨
It’s been great to take some time out in Bali recently whilst settling in to our new place. Also, any known cures for jet lag? All recommendations are welcome! 🌿@traveloka
Peaceful lakeside mornings in one of my favourite countries. See you in Autumn, China 🇨🇳
After an incredible few weeks in South America, I’m finally heading back to Bali. How many pets do you think @sophiapope has adopted whilst I’ve been away? 🐱
Stormy sunsets over Tokyo. I’m currently in the process of recovering my photos from Peru, so hope to be able to share more from that trip really soon! 🤞🏼
The magical Sri Lankan highlands. After an incredible two weeks out in Peru, I’m looking forward to heading back to the UK for some down time. Where’s home for you? 🚂 #whpjourney
The otherworldly landscapes of the Peruvian Andes. In other news, who’s watching the football today? Who are you supporting? 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🇸🇪
There’s nothing like a stare down with a llama to start your day! Also, where’s the llama emoji at? 🧐

node.text: The breathtaking sunrise views up here certainly weren’t helped by the lack of oxygen. If it isn’t already, make sure Peru is right at the top of your list! 🌈
After the last two days of hiking through the Andes, I’m feeling as faded as Grandpa Huang. Once the altitude sickness is gone, I’ll be sharing plenty more from Peru! 🤒

We sat atop the dunes for hours waiting for the clouds to clear - I’d say it was worth it. On another note, super excited to set out on a 2-day hike around the Rainbow Mountains today. Have a great weekend guys! 🌴
Swinging into the weekend like... We’ve had a crazy few days in Peru, I can’t wait to share some photos from the trip as soon as I have time to edit 💃🏼
Chilly mornings amongst the fairytale castles of Europe. Where’s your favourite place to spend the autumn months? 🍁
I left @sophiapope to man the fort and move into our new home in Bali whilst I am in Peru hosting my first photography workshop! Who’s down for a housewarming party when I return? 🎈 @traveloka
🎉 DJI #MavicPro Giveaway! 🎉 ⠀⠀ 🎈And the winner is... @maxime_gobet 🎈
My favourite memory from 2017 was photographing Yarchen Gar, home to the largest concentration of Buddhist nuns and monks in the world. What’s yours? 📸
Hands down one of the coolest villages I’ve ever seen. If I disappear over the summer, you’ll know where to find me 🏚
Quite possibly the world’s most beautiful morning commute 🐃

Thinking back to this moment, I should have taken a tent with me! I haven’t been on social media so much the past few weeks, instead spending some quality time out here in Bali with my brother and his girlfriend - great times. What have you guys been up to?🕴🏼
Great moments watching the sunrise over Shanghai without another person in sight. I’m starting to wonder why it’s not the most crowded time of day 🤔🌆 @fspudong
The night markets in Thailand are some of the best, and most colourful, around. Which city has your favourite nightlife?🌛
It’s looks like our next trip to China will take us to through the north east, just a few hours away from the North Korean border. What are your thoughts on the Singapore Summit? ⛰
Walking home after a long day’s work has never looked better. Where in the world are you guys right now? 👨🏽‍🌾🐃
Exploring the hidden gems of Bali. It’s crazy to think about how much busier this place has become over the last few years. I’m craving somewhere fresh and untouched, any suggestions? 💦
Epic morning scenes over Hong Kong. What’s your favourite city? 🌅
Afternoons like this make the long drives so worth it - it’s great to finally call this island home! What are your plans for the weekend? 🌋
Happy #WorldOceansDay everyone! We started the day by cleaning up litter from one of the local beaches with a great bunch of people - who wants to join on the next one? 🏝
Another mind blowing sunrise on this beautiful island - I feel so grateful to call this place home! Who’s coming to Bali this year? 🌋🌾
Moody mornings in the bluebell forest. We are thinking of heading back to Europe later this year - where should we go?! 🦋 @visitbrussels
What’s the best road you’ve driven down? On another note, I’ve spent the majority of the day curing a hangover - all hugs are most welcome 🌲🌸
25. Sending out a massive thank you to all of those who have sent me messages today, it’s appreciated beyond words. I hope you all have an incredible day! 🎂
The endless layers of The Avatar Mountains. How should I celebrate turning 25 tomorrow? All ideas welcome! 🍃 #whpshine
Bali sure knows how to do a sunset. I shot this using @canonuk’s amazingly light and versatile EOS M50! 🌊 #Sp
High above the chaotic beauty of East Dam. While I love exploring the city, it was great to see the other side of Hong Kong this time around! 💃🏼 @discoverhongkong
One of my favourite places of all time. What’s yours? 🤙🏼

node.text: Magical first light over the rice terraces of Bali. It’s so great to be back! What are your plans for the summer? 🌾
One of my favourite mornings of the year so far. Where’s your favourite place to watch the sunrise? 🗻🚣🏻‍♂️
It was amazing to spend our first morning in Bali strolling around the rice terraces catching up with old friends. What are your plans for the weekend? 🌴
Evenings on the Li River. It’s time for a Q&A! Ask me any questions you like, and I’ll answer them on my stories tomorrow 🎣
Having travelled full time for the best part of two years, I always find myself being drawn back to China. Looking forward to heading back for some autumn colours, who’s in? ☁️ @fshangzhou
Morning strolls through the fairytale bluebell forest of Hallerbos. What’s your favourite colour? 🌲 @visitbrussels
It feels great to be back in the warmth of Hong Kong after a seriously wet few days in China. On another note, this is our last stop before moving to Bali - I’m so excited! 🤯
I didn’t consider myself much of a beach person until I found myself here... though the dog may have helped. Where in the world are guys from? Comment your flag below! 🏝🐶
Afternoon strolls through the railway markets of Thailand. Where’s your favourite place to get lost? 🚂🍌
Photographing the forgotten locals of China is right up there with my favourite things to shoot. How about you? 👨🏽‍🌾🐃 #WHPGetLost
Stormy skies over the Italian Coast meant one thing, consuming way too much pizza. What’s your favourite pizza? I’ll take the four cheese 🍕🧀 @royalcaribbean #SymphonyOfTheSeas #Sp
Can’t wait to head back to this incredible beach in a few weeks time. On another note, my younger brother is headed out to visit me in Bali soon - where do you think I should take him? 💦

Thinking back to these magical times in Myanmar. The last few weeks have been so hectic, going between five countries and preparing to move to Bali has left me little time to sleep, let alone edit any new content. On that note, who’s down to hang in Bali this summer? Looking forward to some serious down time 🤓📕
This shows exactly why I’m a morning person. Super excited to head back to China in a few days time! Any guesses where? 🌼

The beautiful chaos of Hong Kong. I’ve recently started creating both tutorials and blog posts, which will be available very soon! In the meantime, if you guys have any specific topics you’d like me to cover, please let me know in the comments below! 🎨 @discoverhongkong

With each of my audiobooks now finished, I’m desperate to find something new - any suggestions? Ps. While WiFi here in the Philippines is the worst, I’m so excited to share some of my recent adventures with you all 📚

It’s been incredibly refreshing to spend the last week hanging out with friends and soaking up what a country has to offer without a camera in my hand. As you may know, it’s far too easy to get caught up in Instagram, and to forget what really matters. Next stop, Philippines! 🏝
Exploring the Vietnamese countryside the last few days has been nothing short of an incredible adventure. Tell me, where are you guys headed next? ⛰

node.text: We had an insane few days in Hong Kong exploring some of the lesser known gems the city has to offer. What’s your favourite city and why? 🏢 @discoverhongkong

Fading light in one of my favourite places on earth. Just to remind you that there are only a few spaces left on myself and @philngyn’s photography workshop this June/July in Peru with @killaexpeditions! For more info, check out the link in my bio 🏜
Thinking back to great times spent watching these incredibly cute deer chase terribly frightened tourists. Note: always bring extra cookies to Nara! 🦌🍪
A glorious afternoon with Grandpa Huang. Have I convinced you to go to China yet? 🎣
Making my way back to Asia today- it’s only been 3 weeks but I’m already having major withdrawal symptoms. Which one place can you not wait to go back to? 🌏
Stormy skies over the beautiful Manarola with @royalcaribbean. If you had to choose between the coast and mountains, which would it be and why? 🌺🏠 #Sp
Cherry blossom crushing through the Japanese countryside, who’s in? Big thanks to @maanahomes for having us! 🌳🚐🌸
The landlocked lakes of the Dalmatian Coast - definitely one of the most underrated places I’ve been! Which is your favourite spot in Europe? 🌊
HAPPY EARTH DAY! We only have one Earth, so let’s take care of it! Which natural wonder do you want to see most and why? ✨

MY PRINTS ARE NOW LIVE! 🎨
After receiving countless requests over the past few months, and hours at work behind the screen, I have finally opened my print shop, where I’ll be selling a collection of my favourite photos from my recent travels. This weekend, you can get 20% OFF everything using the code ‘ILOVECHEESE’ - link in my bio! 🧀

The vibrant density of Hong Kong. Also, a massive happy birthday to the number one friend, @sophiapope! Forever grateful for your absurd amount of kindness and patience (especially when shooting in places like this!) 🎁🎉
Nothing will beat the look on @sophiapope’s face after watching her reach the summit of this peak - can’t wait to get back to China! Who’s your travel partner in crime? 👫

Moody mornings along the Italian coastline. After the most incredible week exploring the Mediterranean with @royalcaribbean, it’s time to catch up with family and friends back home. Who’s been to Italy?! 🌊 #SymphonyOfTheSeas #Sp
When in Rome... We had the most hectic day exploring the Italian capital with @royalcaribbean, and ate our own body weight in Pizza along the way 🍕 #SymphonyOfTheSeas #Sp
Looking forward to getting back to Bali for the summer! Who’s going to be around? 🌴
Exploring the colourful coast of Cinque Terre with @royalcaribbean. Which house would you choose? #SymphonyOfTheSeas #Sp

After stopping off in Spain and France, we finally made it to my favourite European country- Italy! It’s been an incredible voyage on the ship so far with @royalcaribbean and we can’t wait to explore more. What’s your favourite European country? #SymphonyOfTheSeas #Sp

Announcement: I’m super excited to announce that myself and @philngyn will be hosting our first photography workshop this June/July in Peru with @killaexpeditions! As we traverse snow-capped peaks, turquoise lakes, rainbow mountains, and Machu Picchu, we’ll be teaching you all we have learnt about photography, post-processing techniques, and developing your personal brand through social media. For more info, check out the link in my bio! 🐾 @killaexpeditions

Landing in Barcelona after 20 hours of travel, we headed straight out to explore the city before the crowds. We have just boarded the #SymphonyOfTheSeas and are ready to set sail to Palma, Mallorca - any recommendations?! @royalcaribbean #Sp

As the first light of day struck the mountain side, this guy definitely had the best seat in the house! Super excited to head back to Europe tomorrow to join @royalcaribbean for the maiden voyage of the world’s largest cruise ship, the #SymphonyOfTheSeas. I can’t wait to share the journey with you guys! 🚣🏻‍♂️ #Sp
Japan’s cherry blossom season is something that has to be seen to be believed. Do you know anywhere else like that? 🌸🍃
Misty mornings in the Chinese countryside, I can’t wait to get back next month! Which one place are you dying to get back to? 💃🏻
The karst peaks of southern China are up there with my favourite landscapes to date. Also, Happy Easter everybody! How are you planning on spending the day? 🐰

No matter how many times I return to Mt. Fuji, it always manages to impress me just as much! In other news, me and @sophiapope are looking to head somewhere new in the next few months, any suggestions? 🗻
Afternoon drifting through a sea of pink. With Easter fast approaching, make sure to treat yo self to $15 off your next @mvmt order - just use the code ‘JORDANH15’! 🌸
It was great to break away from the hustle and bustle of Tokyo for a few days to explore the beautiful town of Matsumoto. Which do you prefer, the city or countryside? 🏯

We stumbled across these giants as we were making our way out of the park. Though security were shouting at me telling me I had to leave, I’d say it was worth the trouble! What’s your favourite National Park?! 🌿
As seeing the cherry blossoms in Japan has been on my bucket list for such a long time, I feel incredibly lucky to finally be amongst it! What’s at the top of your list and why? 🌸
To think the people on those tiny boats take that route to work every single morning... I’m signing up, how about you? PS. My print shop will open in one week! 🙋🏻‍♂️
I’m so glad we made it back to Japan to see the cherry blossoms this year! Also, credit to the man rowing out in to the storm - major boyfriend points for you, my friend! 🌸🚣🏻‍♂️

There’s nothing like having the entire place to yourselves - sunrise will always be my favourite time of day! On another note, thanks so much for the overwhelming response to my recent China series, you guys are the best! 🎋
If you don’t hear from me for the next few days, you’ll know where to find me. Also, taking over the @artofvisuals page for the day with some of my favourite shots from Asia, come say hello! 🙋🏻‍♂️
Nothing beats the striking contrast between industrial and rural China, a country that is now like a second home to me. Where’s home for you guys? 🏘

I think we’ve found our new favourite workspace! After getting hundreds of replies to my ‘one thing you dislike about Instagram’ question, I have another - If you could introduce one new feature to improve Instagram, what would it be and why? 📚

It seems Spring has arrived early in Japan! We spent the morning amongst the clouds with this place all to ourselves - a perfect start to the trip. Also, who’s down for a huge story series from China? 🌸

As the sun broke over the distant mountains, a local farmer and his buffalo made their way through the golden mist to cross this ancient bridge - definitely one of my favourite travel memories to date. Tell me one of yours below! 👨🏻‍🌾

The past three weeks in China have been nothing short of incredible. From standing atop karst mountains, to following farmers through the rice terraces, it’s fair to say I’m missing it already. I’d love to know your thoughts on the China series so far - fire away! 🍃
After a hectic last few days exploring Zhangjiajie National Park, we are just about to board our flight to Japan! What are you guys up to right now? 🤘🏼

node.text: I got 99 problems but a bend ain’t one. For real though, this road has 99 of them, and is also known as ‘The Road to Heaven’s Gate’ - I can totally see why! 🐍

Tranquil evenings on the Li River. It was an absolute pleasure to shoot with Grandpa Huang, and to document a tradition that is unfortunately dying out, like many others, due to the increase of tourism in our ever developing world. The fact is, this man now earns far more through tourism that he would have done catching and selling fish locally. What are your thoughts? 🎣
By far my favourite sunrise spot to date. So good, that we’ve already booked our return flights for May. Who’s coming? 🇨🇳

The urban racing stripes of Hong Kong. Having spent the last few days exploring the insane Chinese countryside, it’s been amazing to switch off, yet impossible to upload any new content (1st world problems!). Hope you’re all having an amazing weekend, wherever you are! 🏢
Standing over the towering karst peaks of southern China is an experience like none other. On a side note, this is the last shot I was able to salvage before my drone flew away today 🙋🏻‍♂️

Blue hour over Mt. Fuji. After a few days of torrential rain here in Yangshuo, I’ve been searching for ways to keep myself busy - mostly involving audio books and sleeping. What do you guys do on a rainy day?! 🌧
Last light bursting through the karst peaks of southern China; if only I had a kayak with me! I’m keen to know, what projects are you guys working on right now? 🦖
Now Spring is on its way, I keep wishing I had visited this little village covered in snow! What’s your favourite winter destination? ❄️
Back to where it all began; hands down one of my favourite spots in China! Who else would love to spend the weekend here? 🏚
I can’t wait to go back and explore Japan, this time covered in cherry blossoms! To top it off, my Dad will be joining us for the entire trip. What’s your favourite family holiday memory? 🌸
As the sun dropped towards the horizon and lit up the sky above, this lone farmer made his way back home from a hard day on the terraces. How I’ve missed you, China! 👨🏼‍🌾
Situated in the waters of the Andaman Sea, Ko Panyi is still one of the most charming places I’ve ever visited. If you had to spend a year on this island, which three things would you take and why? 🌊
I wish these incredible leaves were with us all year round! Where are planning on spending the fall this year? 🍁

Foggy sunrises over one of the most magical landscapes I’ve ever seen. It’s been an incredible start to the China trip, and I’m so grateful to have spent it with such an incredible group of people. So, who’s down to join us? 🌻

After a hectic week in Hong Kong, we have finally made it to mainland China! I can’t wait to revisit some of my favourite places on earth, and to show you all more of this amazing country. Stay tuned! 🇨🇳
So it turns out there’s a 50% chance we may not be granted our Chinese visas tomorrow. If so, where should we go next?! I’m thinking somewhere tropical 🌴

Regardless of its popularity, this will always be one of my favourite spots to photograph. Also, massive thanks to everyone who came out for the meet today, I had such an incredible time and it was a pleasure to get to know you all. Where should we host the next one?! 🏚
Cannot thank you all enough for helping me reach 200K! Sending hugs and kisses to you all of you special people. I’d love to follow some new accounts, so tag your favourites below!🍻
Exploring the colourful night markets of Hong Kong. Happy Chinese New Year, everyone! 新年快乐! 🔮

Glorious afternoons in the Italian mountains; I can’t wait to explore more of Europe this year! In other news, I’ve just released an exclusive preset pack on the @canon_photos website. Check the link in my bio to recieve 40% off! 🌲
One of my favourite spots to date. Due to unforeseen circumstances, we’ve got an entire week here in Hong Kong before we fly in to China - any recommendations?! 🌵

node.text: Happy Valentines Day to all of you wonderful people out there, especially @sophiapope! Did anybody get any cute surprises?! 🎁
Having visited this island three years ago, I had no idea how amazing it looked from above! It’s fair to say the past two weeks exploring southern Thailand have been nothing short of incredible 🏝
All my favourite colours in one place. Tomorrow we are heading back to Bangkok for two days, before flying on to Hong Kong! What did you get up to this weekend? 🎨
For more than 200 years, this small fishing village off the south coast of Thailand has clung on to this towering karst island - by far one of most mind blowing landscapes I’ve seen so far! 🎣
Monks are definitely my favourite subject to photograph. How about you? 🙏🏼
Mother Nature at her finest; Krabi has been nothing short of amazing. What’s your favourite sunrise spot? Huge thanks for the stay @eden_villas_krabi ✨
I hope you all had an amazing weekend! Question: If you could go anywhere in the world right now, where would you go and why? @visit.dubai #VisitDubai

Incredibly jealous of whoever lives at the end of this driveway. So, where’s home for you guys? 🌳

node.text: Every time I go back to this place, I can’t help but think of Monsters Inc! What’s your favourite movie?! 🚪 @parkhoteltokyo
As the light mist rolled across the lake and the colours began to dance in the sky, I only wish you could have seen my face. How was your weekend?! 🍂
If the past three weeks in Bali taught me anything, it’s that I absolutely want to live there this year! Any of you down to house share? Let me know! ✨
Missing these fall vibes! I’m having a tough time thinking about where we could visit next - where would you suggest and why? 🌲🍁
After three weeks of constant rain, I think this morning more than made up for it! More importantly, despite reports, Bali is safe. Get yourselves here right now! ⛰
Happy New Year everybody, I hope you all celebrated in style last night! Can’t wait for the year ahead, plenty of exciting announcements coming soon, including my website, tutorials and more 💃🏻
New Year’s Eve tomorrow means only one thing... party at my place! Who’s in? 🎈
Reflection perfection on the Bali coast. I guess it’s time to consider a New Year’s resolution, what’s yours? 💧
Morning strolls through the misty jungles of Ubud. I’m so excited for the new year to arrive, what are your plans for 2018? 🌾
Magical times watching the balloons rise over the Dubai Desert. Can’t wait to fly back here next week! @visit.dubai

I suppose it’s time I started my Christmas shopping. Where are you guys spending the holidays? 🎄

node.text: Reflecting on 2017. What’s your favourite memory of the year so far? 💧
It’s good to be back in the land of the light rays. Thanks again to everybody who took part in my FFA over the last few weeks, I’ve got a ton of incredible entries to go through! 🌴
Day one without a laptop has been a challenge. Do you prefer shooting cities or landscapes? I’m torn between the two! 🏙
We woke up at 5:30am every morning for a week in hope of seeing this. Which is your favourite city?! 🌇
Misty mornings at Mt. Fuji. This guy could possibly have the best view of 2017, what do you think? 🗻
Q&A time! Ask me anything you like. I’ll be putting up the most frequently asked questions on my soon-to-be launched website! 🕯
Brief moments of light in Lauterbrunnen. Who’s down for a Europe road trip next year?! ⛰

Since I began travelling, the Yee Peng Festival is something I’ve always dreamed of seeing with my own eyes. Thankfully, my good friend @mikevisuals did the hard work for me! Be sure to go and check out the #MikeVisualsFFA! 🏮
Who’s excited for Christmas?! Thanks for the good times Shanghai. Next stop, Bali 🌴
Twilight makes for the most magical settings. What's your favourite animal? 🐫✨@visitabudhabi #InAbuDhabi

These colours have made me fall for Japan pretty hard. Who would you share this boat with? 🚣🏼
